{
  "texts": [
    "We will start with the case of a single itinerant electron, i.e., the filling is n = 1/L, where L is the number of sites in a one-dimensional lattice.",
    "Then we will move on to two electrons with n = 2/L, and finally to a finite density n = 1/4.",
    "We use periodic boundary conditions, allowing the use of a quasi-momentum representation in the absence of diagonal disorder.Δk = J/2t 0 k 0 = π/2 k 0 = π/2 (a) (b)In the absence of disorder and at J = 0, the electronic part is diagonal in the quasi-momentum basisĤc = k,σ ϵ k ĉ † k,σ ĉk,σ,(4)where k is the single-particle quasi-momentum chosen to lie in the first Brillouin zone, and the dispersion is (the lattice spacing is set to unity)ϵ k = -2t 0 cos(k).",
    "(5)It is illustrative to rewrite the term in the Hamiltonian that couples the spin of the conduction electrons to the spin of the localized electrons in the quasi-momentum basis.",
    "We use standard definitions for the discrete Fourier transformationĉ † k,σ = 1 √ L L j=1 e ijk ĉ † j,σ,(6)Ŝα k = 1 √ L L j=1 e -ijk Ŝα j,(7)where α = z, +, -."
  ]
